=Description=

"In this episode we talk about imagination, participatory design, barefoot economics, wellbeing, the regenerative triad, our fundamental human needs the role of the commons and even about "thigmomorphogenesis" which was a totally new word for me! ... Inez is a facilitator, educator and consultant in the Human Scale Development Approach (also known as Barefoot Economics), working with communities seeking to improve their quality of life in balance with the Earth’s ecology. With a background in art and performance, her work focuses on the interplay between language, storytelling and culture change to help groups revitalise their ‘radical collective imagination’."


